-Zsuzsanna-A-Marka.png"}}],"mentorsSectionTitle":"Cohort Mentors","mentors":[{"displayName":"Brandon Stafford","prettyUrl":"brandon-stafford","title":"Instructor","affiliation":"Tufts University","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/7stl8UNgb1LkwHNNsMicKR/10316956815455217348b47c58dff4d1/Brandon_S..jpg"}},{"displayName":"César Garcia Saez","prettyUrl":"cesar-garcia-saez","title":"Speaker and researcher","affiliation":"La Hora Maker; Makespace Madrid; ","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/3TSlKqYDPZiNxKucxCcsT9/c441ed4431b692c44bd27aacf9eaae5a/cesar_foto2.jpg"}},{"displayName":"Chris Chronopoulos","prettyUrl":"chris-chronopoulos","title":"Cofounder and board member","affiliation":"Interstitial Technology","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/O2kqQ03wKIKGnZjfvbjuB/c027bd3b0f096cc716a12e995bb1cd58/chris_chronopoulos_in_a_tree_square.jpg"}},{"displayName":"Elizabeth Hendrex","prettyUrl":"elizabeth-hendrex","title":"CEO","affiliation":"Great Scott Gadgets","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/70QSUCy1hd5gRnwkJMYM6z/9bcd68f5208f86ea69d29840c1321c60/Elizabeth_H.png"}},{"displayName":"Huaishu Peng","prettyUrl":"huaishu-peng","title":"Assistant Professor, Computer Science","affiliation":"University of Maryland, College Park","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/7HAMTdiLkasmMdcPav1BTB/125abc2ac8efe677dddbd3d7cbdad788/Huaishu_Peng.jpg"}},{"displayName":"Jinger Zeng","prettyUrl":"jinger-zeng","title":"Board Member 2022-2024","affiliation":"Hackster.io","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/5FZdLNekRotCHhNQq7qeIO/75dce6c688350b7d6b6ec0a199713e11/Jinger_Z.JPG"}},{"displayName":"Joshua Pearce","prettyUrl":"joshua-pearce","title":"Thompson Chair in Information Technology & Innovation and Professor","affiliation":"Western University","image":{"url":"https://images.ctfassets.net/3e0cshhzqlmj/3wwIXJmlf4aygMTT4Esw55/eee060c753e4d8d3c9a8bab3846d16ec/Joshua_Pearce.PNG"}}],"featuredWork":{"resourceTitle":"Enabling Practices","prettyUrl":"enabling-practices","translatedResources":[{"title":"Enabling Practices","subtitle":"Creating and Advocating for Open Source Hardware in Academia","language":"English","shortDescription":{"childrenMarkdownRemark":[{"html":"<p>This documentation is a write up of the 2022-2023 cohort’s collective thoughts and writings, facilitated by Lecia Ductan, Alicia Seidle and Allen Gunn. While creating these documents through the lens of shared ‘Best Practices’, the cohort quickly recognized that their University structures, even limited to an American cohort, were so vastly different, that one set of best practices would not suffice. Some academics owned their research and others did not, some had a form of Tech Transfer Office and others did not, many spanned the landscape of positions one could hold at a University. Some had their Dean’s support in open hardware and others did not. Depending on these differences, “best practices” varied drastically. Some enabling practices may not be a one-size fits all solution, but our fellows and the universities they navigate represent a broad spectrum of American universities. We shifted the terminology to enabling practices to encompass more types of universities, where “best” would imply that one university type would be prioritized with which practices work in that system.</p>"}]},"buttonText":"Download","buttonUrl":"https://resources.oshwa.org/files/enabling-practices.pdf"}],"resourceImage":{"gatsbyImage":{"images":{"sources":[{"srcSet":"/_gatsby/image/1e8c4e88d9a7bc28374e7c0cbd78f3f4/1617fd6666d9cab28d0937e3e10342ed/enabling-practices-cover.avif?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2F3e0cshhzqlmj%2F1Jjv4aaEu48Zr5Uh65txmH%2F442343df16e81912ec35fc6af1f18986%2Fenabling-practices-cover.jpg&a=w%3D150%26h%3D194%26fm%3Davif%26q%3D75&cd=2024-06-05T21%3A53%3A39.982Z 150w,/_gatsby/image/1e8c4e88d9a7bc28374e7c0cbd78f3f4/869bd1618c27e6d74352bf81db857729/enabling-practice